<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-12219] Potential race condition in InMemoryKeyValueStore</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-12219</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8802&quot; title=&quot;ConcurrentSkipListMap shows performance regression in cache and in-memory store&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-8802&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-8802&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (included in &lt;a href=&quot;https://downloads.apache.org/kafka/2.4.0/RELEASE_NOTES.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;2.4.0 release&lt;/a&gt;), &lt;tt&gt;ConcurrentSkipListMap&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;tt&gt;InMemoryKeyValueStore&lt;/tt&gt; was reverted into &lt;tt&gt;TreeMap&lt;/tt&gt; for performance issues. However, the &lt;tt&gt;synchronized&lt;/tt&gt; keyword for &lt;tt&gt;reverseRange&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;reverseAll&lt;/tt&gt; methods were omitted when adding the reverse range methods in 2.7, leaving possibility of race condition.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
